Quoting Jennifer Carney <jcarney@NASFT.org>:

> Hi Jeff,
>
> The 2011 Winter Fancy Food Show will be held at the Moscone Center  
> in San Francisco from January 16-18, 2011. The cost for a booth is  
> $34.00 per square foot, so a 10x10 (100 square feet) would cost you  
> $3,400.00.
>
> Membership:
> Key requirements for acceptance include:
> *	Your company must have been actively selling its products in the  
> specialty food trade for one year
> *	You need to submit retail product samples
> *	A non-refundable $100.00 application fee
> *	Name NASFT as an additional insured on your insurance policy
>
> Annual membership dues are inexpensive ($200-$600) and are based on  
> your annual sales volume:
> o	$200 equal sales under $1million
> o	$400 equal sales between $1million - $5million
> o	$600 equal sales over $5million
>
> As a member of the NASFT you can participate in our great programs  
> that non-members cannot take part in.  These programs include:
> -"What's New/What's Hot", our new product launch area
> -Business Builders 1-1 ,which is one on one interviews with key  
> buyers that take place before the show even starts
> -Sofi Awards , These awards are the highest honor in the specialty  
> food industry. They recognize the outstanding foods and beverages of  
> the year that demonstrate top quality, taste and overall appeal.  
> "sofi" stands for Specialty Outstanding Food Innovation -   
> http://www.specialtyfood.com/do/focused/SofiAwards
>
>
> When exhibiting in one of our shows, you will receive a  
> complimentary booth package which includes your carpet, 2 tables, 2  
> chairs, company id sign and wastebasket.  I have attached a  
> membership application for you to review.  If you have any further  
> questions regarding membership please contact Claire Cholmondeley at  
> 646-878-0122 or ccholmondeley@nasft.org . Thank you.
>
>
